  "A movie theater sells adult tickets for $10 and child tickets for $6. If 50 tickets were sold for a total of $380, how many adult tickets were sold?": "",
  "25": "",
  "32": "",
  "18": "",
  "20": "",
  "Let a = adult, c = child. System: a + c = 50 and 10a + 6c = 380. From the first: c = 50 - a. Substitute: 10a + 6(50 - a) = 380 → 4a = 80 → a = 20. Verify: 10(20) + 6(30) = 200 + 180 = 380.": "",
  "A store sells notebooks for $3 and pens for $1. A student buys 10 items for $18. How many notebooks were purchased?": "",
  "6": "",
  "3": "",
  "4": "",
  "5": "",
  "Let n = notebooks and p = pens. n + p = 10 and 3n + p = 18. Subtract: 2n = 8, so n = 4. The student bought 4 notebooks and 6 pens.": "",
  "Two friends are 60 miles apart and drive toward each other. One drives 40 mph and the other 20 mph. When do they meet?": "",
  "3 hours": "",
  "2 hours": "",
  "1 hour": "",
  "1.5 hours": "",
  "Combined speed is 40 + 20 = 60 mph. Distance = rate × time: 60 = 60t, so t = 1 hour.": "",
  "A farmer has chickens and cows. He counts 30 heads and 80 legs. How many cows does he have?": "",
  "15": "",
  "10": "",
  "12": "",
  "Let c = chickens and w = cows. c + w = 30 and 2c + 4w = 80. From the first: c = 30 - w. Substitute: 2(30 - w) + 4w = 80 → 60 - 2w + 4w = 80 → 2w = 20 → w = 10 cows.": "",
  "A chemist mixes a 20% acid solution with a 50% acid solution to get 30 liters of a 30% solution. How many liters of the 20% solution are needed?": "",
  "10 liters": "",
  "20 liters": "",
  "25 liters": "",
  "15 liters": "",
  "Let x = liters of 20%, y = liters of 50%. System: x + y = 30 and 0.20x + 0.50y = 9. From the first: y = 30 - x. Substitute: 0.20x + 0.50(30 - x) = 9 → 0.20x + 15 - 0.50x = 9 → -0.30x = -6 → x = 20 liters.": "",
  "A concert has $5 lawn seats and $15 reserved seats. If 200 tickets generate $2,000 in revenue, how many reserved seats were sold?": "",
  "75": "",
  "50": "",
  "100": "",
  "150": "",
  "Let L = lawn, R = reserved. L + R = 200 and 5L + 15R = 2000. Substitute L = 200 - R: 5(200 - R) + 15R = 2000 → 1000 + 10R = 2000 → R = 100.": "",
  "A school is ordering pizzas and drinks for a party. Pizzas cost $12 each and drinks cost $2 each. They order 20 items for $120. How many pizzas did they order?": "",
  "8": "",
  "Let p = pizzas, d = drinks. p + d = 20 and 12p + 2d = 120. From the first: d = 20 - p. Substitute: 12p + 2(20 - p) = 120 → 12p + 40 - 2p = 120 → 10p = 80 → p = 8.": "",
  "A boat travels 24 miles downstream in 2 hours and 24 miles upstream in 3 hours. What is the speed of the boat in still water?": "",
  "6 mph": "",
  "10 mph": "",
  "12 mph": "",
  "8 mph": "",
  "Downstream: b + c = 24/2 = 12. Upstream: b - c = 24/3 = 8. Add: 2b = 20, so b = 10 mph. The current is 2 mph.": "",
  "A cashier has $5 bills and $10 bills totaling $95. She has 13 bills in all. How many $10 bills does she have?": "",
  "7": "",
  "Let f = number of $5 bills, t = number of $10 bills. f + t = 13 and 5f + 10t = 95. From the first: f = 13 - t. Substitute: 5(13 - t) + 10t = 95 → 65 - 5t + 10t = 95 → 5t = 30 → t = 6.": "",
  "An investment of $5,000 is split between two accounts. One earns 4% interest and the other 6%. If the total annual interest is $260, how much was invested at 6%?": "",
  "$2,000": "",
  "$3,000": "",
  "$4,000": "",
  "$2,500": "",
  "Let x = amount at 4%, y = amount at 6%. x + y = 5000 and 0.04x + 0.06y = 260. Substitute x = 5000 - y: 0.04(5000 - y) + 0.06y = 260 → 200 - 0.04y + 0.06y = 260 → 0.02y = 60 → y = $3,000.": ""
